1
00:02:03,459 --> 00:02:05,019
What's that oddball scheming now?

2
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,560
Use that birdbrain of yours to think.

3
00:02:10,819 --> 00:02:12,439
She's not a wealth manager for nothing.

4
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:14,020
Too stingy to spend her own money,

5
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:15,699
so she's giving away the Mid-Autumn gifts

6
00:02:15,699 --> 00:02:16,539
from her workplace instead.

7
00:02:17,099 --> 00:02:18,080
Using the company's stuff

8
00:02:18,319 --> 00:02:20,460
beats begging a man for money.

9
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,419
You, Mrs. birdbrain Tycoon,

10
00:02:22,419 --> 00:02:23,120
came back this time

11
00:02:23,139 --> 00:02:24,139
being awfully stingy, huh?

12
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,259
Can't put food on the table?

13
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:28,500
If you want Grand Elder Qi to speak up for us,

14
00:02:29,099 --> 00:02:30,960
the gifts have to be presentable.

15
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:33,120
That stuff of yours,

16
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:34,780
still stamped with the bank's logo?

17
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:36,620
You think Grand Elder Qi would even glance at it?

18
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:37,900
Fine.

19
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,740
You go handle this then.

20
00:02:39,979 --> 00:02:41,000
You go talk to Grand Elder Qi.

21
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,340
I'll pay AND do the work?

22
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,280
Then what are you gonna do?

23
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:46,819
I'm going to see Old Miao.

24
00:02:49,879 --> 00:02:51,460
Your old backup?

25
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:52,620
So lame.

26
00:02:54,759 --> 00:02:55,879
I hear Old Miao

27
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:58,000
is transferring to the county government next year.

28
00:02:58,879 --> 00:03:00,139
Think about it, picking Old Miao back then

29
00:03:00,699 --> 00:03:01,979
would've been way better than Yin Zhiqiang.

30
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,620
Back then, Old Miao

31
00:03:03,719 --> 00:03:05,360
insisted on staying in this backwater.

32
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:07,060
Otherwise, you two would've been together.

33
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,479
Back in the day,

34
00:03:08,919 --> 00:03:11,460
Old Miao was a spirited young man too.

35
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:12,840
Everyone

36
00:03:12,939 --> 00:03:13,939
has their own fate.

37
00:03:16,340 --> 00:03:18,439
But Old Miao back then

38
00:03:18,439 --> 00:03:19,439
really was quite dashing.

39
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,580
But men, you know,

40
00:03:21,699 --> 00:03:22,560
change more than women do.

41
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,240
He's probably bald by now,

42
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,000
with a big beer belly,

43
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,199
all bloated and out of shape.

44
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:26,800
Let me tell you,

45
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,939
if it weren't for Xiaofang,

46
00:03:28,159 --> 00:03:29,520
I wouldn't go see him for the world.

47
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:30,560
What?

48
00:03:31,259 --> 00:03:33,439
Afraid to ruin your first love's image?

49
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,259
Nothing more to say.

50
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,020
You know what?

51
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,020
Yin Zhiqiang

52
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:44,199
found another woman.

53
00:03:45,379 --> 00:03:46,120
So what if he did?

54
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,840
We're already divorced.

55
00:03:47,919 --> 00:03:48,659
He can date whoever he wants.

56
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:50,400
She's pregnant again.

57
00:03:51,639 --> 00:03:52,300
Who's pregnant?

58
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,020
Jingjing's stepmother.

59
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,659
Fast work.

60
00:04:01,219 --> 00:04:01,580
Mom,

61
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:03,020
give her a call

62
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:04,599
and see if Jingjing's back.

63
00:04:04,599 --> 00:04:05,919
Have her come celebrate the holiday.

64
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,639
Over there, with the stepmom

65
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:08,780
and the new baby,

66
00:04:09,340 --> 00:04:10,879
who's got time for her?

67
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,219
Here with us,

68
00:04:12,379 --> 00:04:13,719
we're her real family after all.

69
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:14,780
Mom,

70
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:16,519
I already called.

71
00:04:16,699 --> 00:04:18,220
She told me she's not coming back.

72
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:19,920
Even if she does come back,

73
00:04:19,939 --> 00:04:21,259
she'll just visit her grandma.

74
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:22,480
She won't come here.

75
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:24,259
That child and I

76
00:04:24,839 --> 00:04:25,720
are so distant.

77
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,439
You're her real mother.

78
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:31,339
Start fawning and care for her more.

79
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:33,860
Even a stone will warm up

80
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:35,800
if you hold it close.

81
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:39,819
You two,

82
00:04:40,139 --> 00:04:41,199
where are you off to?

83
00:04:41,519 --> 00:04:42,579
Where else?

84
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:45,220
Going to feel them out for Xiaofang.

85
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:45,980
Mom,

86
00:04:46,399 --> 00:04:47,300
the Qi family still

87
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:48,220
hasn't given us any answer.

88
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,279
They're clearly stalling.

89
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,480
Just waiting for us to show up

90
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,279
and beg them.

91
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,500
This is Xiaofang's own business.

92
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:57,160
A bunch of you grown-ups

93
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,279
butting in like this.

94
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,139
A perfectly good relationship,

95
00:05:00,439 --> 00:05:02,379
and you're all messing it up.

96
00:05:18,019 --> 00:05:18,519
Xiaowei

97
00:05:23,579 --> 00:05:23,980
What is it?

98
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,259
Why are you staring at me?

99
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:27,579
I'm trying to see what you're thinking.

100
00:05:30,019 --> 00:05:30,639
I found this

101
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:31,620
really fun place.

102
00:05:31,699 --> 00:05:32,519
You'll definitely love it.

103
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:33,300
I'll take you there sometime.

104
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,740
That's not what I mean.

105
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,680
Why do I feel like since you came back,

106
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,939
you're like a different person?

107
00:05:43,399 --> 00:05:44,139
How have I changed?

108
00:05:44,379 --> 00:05:45,720
My feelings for you have never changed.

109
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,079
I'm not talking about how you treat me.

110
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,240
I mean how you treat yourself.

111
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,060
I...

112
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,699
I'm just thinking about

113
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,779
the bride price thing.

114
00:05:57,980 --> 00:05:59,519
I want you to marry with dignity.

115
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,720
The talk with your dad didn't go well.

116
00:06:05,439 --> 00:06:06,220
Just give me some more time.

117
00:06:06,639 --> 00:06:08,319
I haven't forgotten what I promised in Shenzhen.

118
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:09,600
About the money,

119
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:11,000
I'll fight for it to the very end.

120
00:06:11,699 --> 00:06:13,259
The thing is, I don't know

121
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:14,899
how much my dad will put up.

122
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,339
So I want to work harder

123
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,519
back in Shenzhen,

124
00:06:17,779 --> 00:06:18,720
and save up more money.

125
00:06:19,699 --> 00:06:21,740
What matters isn't the wedding or bride price.

126
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,540
It's about welcoming the one you love.

127
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,259
Don't put too much pressure on yourself.

128
00:06:30,019 --> 00:06:31,319
I've got a battle plan.

129
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,339
You have a battle plan too?

130
00:06:35,759 --> 00:06:36,379
What is it?

131
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,560
I've done the math.

132
00:06:40,939 --> 00:06:42,240
I make five thousand a month.

133
00:06:42,459 --> 00:06:43,180
I save three thousand.

134
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:44,339
In a year,

135
00:06:44,339 --> 00:06:45,379
I can save over 30,000.

136
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:47,379
And I've got you too.

137
00:06:48,399 --> 00:06:48,860
So,

138
00:06:50,259 --> 00:06:51,459
we should still ask for the bride price, right?

139
00:06:54,019 --> 00:06:55,220
If we have it,

140
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:56,579
our little family's startup fund

141
00:06:56,579 --> 00:06:57,199
would be more comfortable.

142
00:06:57,399 --> 00:06:57,879
That's a good thing.

143
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,180
But if this causes

144
00:07:00,180 --> 00:07:01,240
bad feelings,

145
00:07:01,519 --> 00:07:02,139
then it's not worth it.

146
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,399
What matters is we're on the same page.

147
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:05,439
Nothing else matters.

148
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,100
Did you bring your ID?

149
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:10,899
No, why?

150
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,160
Our marriage has nothing to do with the bride price.

151
00:07:13,639 --> 00:07:14,100
In a bit,

152
00:07:14,139 --> 00:07:15,480
go home and get your ID.

153
00:07:15,939 --> 00:07:17,220
We'll go register for marriage right away.

154
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:19,680
Are we really going to elope?

155
00:07:20,259 --> 00:07:21,920
After registering, we run back to Shenzhen.

156
00:07:24,019 --> 00:07:25,000
We're not going to elope.

157
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,019
We're getting married the proper way.

158
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,319
Once we're married,

159
00:07:29,459 --> 00:07:30,500
whatever they say won't matter.

160
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:33,819
Xiaofang's already pregnant before marriage.

161
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,300
Now, if we send Xiaofang

162
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,160
off to the Qi family,

163
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:37,600
then where does that leave

164
00:07:37,699 --> 00:07:38,220
the Yang family's face?

165
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:40,100
The Qis want a bargain without paying.

166
00:07:40,819 --> 00:07:42,259
With Qi Xiaowei's little salary,

167
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,000
he can barely support himself.

168
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:45,160
Not asking for money?

169
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:46,500
When Xiaofang has the baby,

170
00:07:46,819 --> 00:07:47,920
they'll count on us for everything.

171
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:49,500
Both of you, stop arguing.

172
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,100
Listen to me, don't approach anyone.

173
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:53,699
Getting a marriage certificate now

174
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:56,600
doesn't even need the household registration.

175
00:07:57,100 --> 00:08:00,040
The country promotes freedom of marriage.

176
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,779
Whatever Xiaofang decides,

177
00:08:02,079 --> 00:08:03,279
we'll support her.

178
00:08:04,079 --> 00:08:04,639
Mom,

179
00:08:04,939 --> 00:08:06,600
you enjoy your freedom here.

180
00:08:06,939 --> 00:08:07,540
I'm heading out.

181
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:10,199
That's for our holiday meal.

182
00:08:10,439 --> 00:08:11,860
There's still one more left, right?

183
00:08:12,079 --> 00:08:12,699
She said the stuff

184
00:08:12,699 --> 00:08:13,839
I brought from the company,

185
00:08:13,839 --> 00:08:14,420
isn't presentable enough.

186
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:14,819
True enough.

187
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:16,560
Old Miao's been eyeing

188
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:17,699
your cured ham.

189
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:19,040
I'll take one over to him.

190
00:08:19,939 --> 00:08:20,699
Mom,

191
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,339
what he's eyeing

192
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,139
isn't just our cured ham.

193
00:08:24,279 --> 00:08:26,980
It's also your eldest daughter's long legs.

194
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:28,399
You birdbrain.

195
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:31,759
Now you're worrying about your sister?

196
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,440
Mom, you're so biased.

197
00:08:35,580 --> 00:08:36,659
You only come down hard on me,

198
00:08:36,659 --> 00:08:37,580
always siding with Yang Fanyan.

199
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,440
Am I adopted or something?

200
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,259
Listen to yourself.

201
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,919
You're really hitting me?

202
00:08:43,879 --> 00:08:45,919
You haven't sorted out your own life,

203
00:08:46,539 --> 00:08:47,159
if you ask me,

204
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,200
Xiaofang's got her life together better than you.

205
00:08:53,919 --> 00:08:55,500
Xiaowei, I don't want to go back to Shenzhen.

206
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,419
Not going back to Shenzhen?

207
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,059
What are you worried about?

208
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:06,860
I'm worried.

209
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:11,259
If we don't go back to Shenzhen,

210
00:09:12,179 --> 00:09:13,759
how will we earn a living?

211
00:09:13,879 --> 00:09:14,860
I've already thought about that.

212
00:09:15,299 --> 00:09:16,480
With our income,

213
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,379
raising a kid in Shenzhen

214
00:09:17,379 --> 00:09:18,379
would be way too hard.

215
00:09:18,980 --> 00:09:19,659
But look,

216
00:09:21,139 --> 00:09:21,720
these here

217
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,320
are just common herbs.

218
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,259
They're not worth much.

219
00:09:24,659 --> 00:09:25,980
I can't really move around right now.

220
00:09:26,379 --> 00:09:27,600
Back when my grandpa was alive,

221
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:28,899
he'd hike deep into the mountains.

222
00:09:28,980 --> 00:09:30,539
The herbs there are rare and valuable.

223
00:09:31,019 --> 00:09:31,759
Selling herbs...

224
00:09:32,759 --> 00:09:33,080
Well,

225
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,720
how much can they really bring in?

226
00:09:35,259 --> 00:09:36,700
You can't live off that your whole life.

227
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,259
But I've still got you, don't I?

228
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,460
You're an artist.

229
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:40,940
Look at how beautiful the scenery is here.

230
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:42,440
You can paint tons of pictures.

231
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:44,120
And those paintings can sell for money too.

232
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:54,080
Well, you've got it all figured out.

233
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:56,539
I really have faith in us.

234
00:09:56,879 --> 00:09:58,000
I believe with what we're capable of,

235
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,259
we'll definitely make it work.

236
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:00,940
And we won't be under their control.

237
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:01,919
Whatever they want to stir up,

238
00:10:01,919 --> 00:10:02,759
let them stir it up.

239
00:10:31,039 --> 00:10:32,820
Director, what notice came in this time?

240
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:34,039
Here, see for yourself.

241
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:48,860
Yanzi.

242
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:51,559
Is that you?

243
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:55,440
You're funny.

244
00:10:56,379 --> 00:10:57,620
Who else would it be?

245
00:10:59,080 --> 00:10:59,919
Your skin got fairer.

246
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,440
You... you got stronger.

247
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,559
Right now,

248
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:05,919
I'm doing pretty well.

249
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:08,899
That's good then.

250
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:11,580
What's good about it?

251
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:12,659
Everything's good.

252
00:11:15,259 --> 00:11:16,559
Are you gonna keep me holding this?

253
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,220
You even brought something.

254
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,379
Director Miao's getting promoted.

255
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:26,019
Local goods aren't good enough for you now.

256
00:11:26,399 --> 00:11:27,019
Not at all, not at all.

257
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,919
I've been thinking about you.

258
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,820
Thinking about your family's cured ham.

259
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:38,019
It's the one and only

260
00:11:38,039 --> 00:11:38,679
in the whole world.

261
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:43,960
Aren't you gonna invite me in?

262
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,100
Come on, come on in.

263
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,600
Isn't this what we played with as kids?

264
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,340
So nostalgic.

265
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:52,899
Yeah.

266
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:54,720
I put in a lot of effort

267
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,840
to gather all these things together.

268
00:11:58,340 --> 00:11:59,340
Not bad!

269
00:11:59,879 --> 00:12:02,539
A proper village history museum.

270
00:12:04,039 --> 00:12:06,460
It's also to answer the call from above,

271
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,960
to bring our village

272
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:08,860
some cultural tourism,

273
00:12:09,519 --> 00:12:10,519
and to find our village

274
00:12:10,639 --> 00:12:11,679
some new opportunities.

275
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:13,720
Only you could do it.

276
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:15,259
You've been sharp since childhood.

277
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:18,220
You've built our village's industries

278
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,820
into something impressive.

279
00:12:21,879 --> 00:12:22,820
Coming back this time,

280
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,419
I'm kinda thinking of not leaving.

281
00:12:24,899 --> 00:12:25,580
I feel like

282
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,779
life in the village

283
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,940
compared to the big city

284
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:28,740
isn't any worse.

285
00:12:31,759 --> 00:12:32,139
